# Go

- Handle errors explicitly; wrap with `%w` when propagating; avoid ignoring returned errors.
- Prefer small interfaces at call sites; avoid unnecessary exported symbols.
- Use `context.Context` for cancellation and deadlines on I/O and RPC.
- Format with `gofmt`; run `go vet` and tests before considering work done.
- Avoid global mutable state; use dependency injection where it clarifies tests.
